You can spawn individual async tasks with `tokio::spawn` and then `.await` their handles. Alternatively, if you want to wait for all of them at the same time (without knowing which one completes first), use `tokio::join!`:

```rust
let handle1 = tokio::spawn(async { /* task 1 */ });
let handle2 = tokio::spawn(async { /* task 2 */ });

let (result1, result2) = tokio::join!(handle1, handle2);
println!("Both tasks completed: {} and {}
", result1?, result2?);
```Or if you want to pick the first one that completes, use `tokio::select!`:

```rust
tokio::select! {
    result = handle1 => println!("Task 1 finished first: {:?}", result),
    result = handle2 => println!("Task 2 finished first: {:?}", result),
}
```That gives you fine control over async concurrency.

